Not really. No one's mentioned the irony that he wants to take window labels off of the interface even though that would make it kind of hard for newbies to understand what they're for, and yet a majority of the &quot;bugs&quot; he speaks out against are just him being inept. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 942<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 3:37:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1433.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ROFL</span><hr size=1> Anyone that can't figure out what the windows mean in under 0.1s really should just hop right back on the short bus.  The labels are pointless.  I can't recall a single person ever having trouble with what any of the windows in the old UI meant in 3+ years of playing with it.  And, I've run into some pretty clueless newbies, too.<br>
<br>
It's poor engineering design, too.  It breaks the 80/20 rule: you don't design something for the 20% case, you build it for the 80% case.  Since the label only matters to perhaps 0.001% of the people out there and only matters for at most a few seconds when playing for the very first time, it's a waste of space.<br>
<br>
No, the issue really is that most of them aren't really bugs, they're just poor UI design.  Most fall into the category of changes that don't deliver any new functionality; it's just change for the sake of change.  He's gone balistic over trivia.  The only outright bug I'm aware of is the /language bug. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 528<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 3:43:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1433.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ROFL</span><hr size=1> It works both ways. If you can't figure out how to change to a third-person perspective, or re-size your chat window, you are in the minority. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 508<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 3:57:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1433.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ROFL</span><hr size=1> The only valid point I see in here is the chatfontsize thing. If he can't get the same font size as he's used to, well that sucks. Personally I hate that I can't get the old hitsmode functionality back... I have to make a new chat window that I'm always clicking on by accident. And I wish they'd fix /camp desktop and /lang. Those are little nagging annoyances.<br>
<br>
Almost everything else in that list can be worked around by modifying the UI files, though. If you can't figure out how to do it yourself, there are plenty of canned mods available for download online. You can remove the title bars. You can make windows transparent (I mean transparent background, not alpha fade which fades everything including, say, spell icons which sucks). You can change your spell icons, hell on my screen I actually have the names of the buffs listed next to them so I don't have to right-click to see what they are. Pretty sure you can change the number of spells per page in your book too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uyiar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yiar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 4:03:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1433.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ROFL</span><hr size=1> I love the point about Combine Gate/Portal/Circle/Translocate<br>
